Port Nick
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:sailors' and settlers' elliptical form of Port Nicholson, the early name for Wellington and its harbour. <i>Port Nick</i> became (1845 at least) Maori <i>Poniki, Poneke.</i>
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
