Citations
Date: 11/9/1869
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: Shorty after the first sale of land in the township, where sod and thatch whares were beginning to spring up, an old woman, a recent arrival, gravely asked a passer-by to tell her how long it would be before the township was as large as "Port Nick," at which he laughed aloud; but if things go on improving as they have done for the next few years, the old woman's question may not appear so ridiculous after all.
